title: >>> The NUMBERS
body_text:
Similiarly to last week, a prediction was thrown out concerning the number of players that would attend DODGEBALL 15. It was said that more would attend than at DODGEBALL XTWO, which held the record with 42. Now the holiday did indeed help, but DODGEBALL 15 did not defeat XTWO. However, attendance was still outstanding, putting DODGEBALL 15 in second place with an incredible 37.
The numbers in recent weeks have been staggering to say the least. If you look at past events, you will notice the numbers have increased and have certainly been more consistent in recent weeks.
DODGEBALL DAY 1 (09/03): 12 Players
DODGEBALL DAY 2 (09/04): 16 Players
DODGEBALL DAY 3 (09/10): 20 Players
DODGEBALL DAY 4 (09/17): 24 Players
D-DAY 5 (09/24): 27 Players
D-DAY VI (10/01): 30 Players
DODGEBALL 7 (10/08): 15 Players
DODGEBALL 8 (10/15): 28 Players
DODGEBALL 9 (10/22): 19 Players
DODGEBALL X (10/28): 24 Players
DODGEBALL XONE (11/04): 33 Players
DODGEBALL XTWO (11/05): 42 Players
DODGEBALL 13 (11/12): 33 Players
DODGEBALL XIV (11/19): 31 Players
DODGEBALL 15 (11/26): 37 Players
DODGEBALL X6 (12/03): ???
Let the facts speak for themself. Even though DODGEBALL 7 and DODGEBALL 9 had "low" attendance, do not forget that they were "Wet Wars". The pouring rain and high winds did not affect any of the challengers that played on those nights. All other events, especially since DODGEBALL XONE, have seen the numbers fly through the roof.
That brings up the main question ...
How many players do you think will attend DODGEBALL X6?
*Leave a comment with your prediction*
The first event of the new month is going to be a good one. The history of dodgeball grows with each passing week, and DODGEBALL X6 will add to it.
